## table card | doc="A card instance. phase is a 3-value enum (triage/active/terminal) that categorises flow-bound value-cards used in ref attributes (status='Done' → terminal; status='New idea' → triage; status='Doing' → active). Drives the predicate compiler's has_phase op and the legacy notTerminal alias (phase='terminal'), the TransitionBar UI buckets via (from.phase, to.phase) pairs, and the default-create-status resolution chain. Defaults 'triage' for new value-cards (admins flip to active/terminal at creation time). Cards that are not flow-bound value-cards (tasks, projects, persons, …) carry the default but the value is never consulted."

### meta
name_attribute
title

### columns
