## table activity_sink_state | doc="Per-sink high-water mark + last-error for the activity pump. Separated from the sink card's attributes so the pointer can advance every push without writing a fresh attr_update activity row on the sink itself (which would re-enter the activity stream and cause feedback). last_activity_id is the largest activity.id this sink has successfully delivered downstream; the pump scans WHERE id > last_activity_id."

