## function cas_missing_chunks_batch | doc="cas.missing_chunks — anti-join input addresses against cas_blob; result.missing[] preserves input ordinality so duplicated input addresses appear duplicated in the output (matches the legacy Go-side unnest behaviour). Empty / missing addresses[] returns missing=[]." | path="functions/cas_missing_chunks_batch.sql"
## function _canon_card_ref | doc="Canonicalise a jsonb value against an attribute_def.value_type. card_ref string-of-digits becomes a JSON number; card_ref[] applies elementwise; other shapes pass through. Mirrors schema.Snapshot.CanonicalizeValue." | path="functions/canon_card_ref.sql" | arg_types="jsonb, text"
## function _ph_push | doc="Placeholder-bag append primitive for card_compile_predicate (A13 / BE-H2 safe increment). Appends a value to the JSONB params bag and returns (new_bag, 0-based index) so no predicate leaf hand-counts a placeholder offset. Declared before card_compile_predicate." | path="functions/ph_push.sql" | arg_types="jsonb, jsonb"
## function card_compile_predicate | doc="Recursive predicate-tree compiler used by card_select_with_attributes_batch. Walks the v2 tree (connective / leaf / snippet) and emits a SQL boolean fragment plus an accumulated JSONB params bag. Mirrors the Go-side card.CompileTree." | path="functions/card_compile_predicate.sql" | arg_types="jsonb, jsonb, bigint[]"
## function card_select_with_attributes_batch | doc="card.select_with_attributes — SPA's main read path. Compiles the v1 where[] / v2 tree via card_compile_predicate, layers in optional personal_sort / routed_to_me joins + ordering LATERALs, EXECUTEs the dynamic SQL, returns each input's rows as a JSONB array under result.rows. Per-actor visibility predicate (B7) AND-joined." | path="functions/card_select_with_attributes_batch.sql"
## function flow_list_batch | doc="flow.list — list flow rows, optionally filtered by scope_card_id (project) and / or attribute_def_id. Joined to attribute_def for the display name." | path="functions/flow_list_batch.sql"
